The Grammy nominations have just been announced and it’s a newcomers fest. On the homefront, our very own Burna Boy got a nomination for ‘Best World Music Album’ category. The Grammys take place on January 26 at the Staples Center in Los Angeles. They’ll be hosted by Alicia Keys and will air live on CBS. WORLD MUSIC Best World Music Album For albums containing at least 51% playing time of new vocal or instrumental World Music recordings. GECE Altin Gün WHAT HEAT Bokanté & Metropole Orkest Conducted By Jules Buckley AFRICAN GIANT Burna Boy FANM D’AYITI Nathalie Joachim With Spektral Quartet CELIA Angelique Kidjo